WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.360 --> 00:00:01.770
- Vibe coding lets you build apps

2
00:00:01.770 --> 00:00:05.550
that solve your work problems,
but why do we call it that?

3
00:00:05.550 --> 00:00:08.340
Well, it's a fun way for you
to build something helpful

4
00:00:08.340 --> 00:00:10.710
without needing to code.

5
00:00:10.710 --> 00:00:12.660
All you have to do is know the vibe

6
00:00:12.660 --> 00:00:14.580
of what you want to achieve.

7
00:00:14.580 --> 00:00:16.710
Okay, there's a little
more to it than that,

8
00:00:16.710 --> 00:00:19.020
and that's what I'm here to show you.

9
00:00:19.020 --> 00:00:21.690
See, a year ago, when
these models had come out,

10
00:00:21.690 --> 00:00:25.290
I wanted to see if I could
make a childhood game of mine.

11
00:00:25.290 --> 00:00:27.810
And I didn't know the
limits of what was possible,

12
00:00:27.810 --> 00:00:32.010
but for three days I persevered
through all sorts of errors,

13
00:00:32.010 --> 00:00:35.493
and by the end of it,
somehow that game was made.

14
00:00:36.330 --> 00:00:38.790
Now, fast-forward a year from then.

15
00:00:38.790 --> 00:00:41.940
Today, if I just give
the model one screenshot,

16
00:00:41.940 --> 00:00:44.133
it can make the entire game for me.

17
00:00:45.000 --> 00:00:47.340
It's wild how fast
these things are moving.

18
00:00:47.340 --> 00:00:50.340
And so how do you bring that to your work?

19
00:00:50.340 --> 00:00:51.780
To give you an idea,

20
00:00:51.780 --> 00:00:54.810
we'll practice building
a few apps together.

21
00:00:54.810 --> 00:00:58.110
Here's a sneak preview of
the three apps we'll build.

22
00:00:58.110 --> 00:01:00.900
The first app I like
to call The Tiebreaker.

23
00:01:00.900 --> 00:01:02.280
This is an app that I built

24
00:01:02.280 --> 00:01:05.610
specifically to help
make tricky decisions.

25
00:01:05.610 --> 00:01:07.560
You'll customize it so that it understands

26
00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:10.170
your preferred approach
to decision-making.

27
00:01:10.170 --> 00:01:12.030
For example, do you like to compare

28
00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:13.710
two options side by side,

29
00:01:13.710 --> 00:01:15.660
or are you someone who likes to go deep

30
00:01:15.660 --> 00:01:18.090
on a cost-benefit analysis?

31
00:01:18.090 --> 00:01:20.160
This app will help you
analyze your options

32
00:01:20.160 --> 00:01:23.400
so that you feel good
about your decisions.

33
00:01:23.400 --> 00:01:27.150
The second app is a Marketing
Materials Generator.

34
00:01:27.150 --> 00:01:29.160
Need creative for an upcoming launch,

35
00:01:29.160 --> 00:01:31.470
or a promotion, or an announcement?

36
00:01:31.470 --> 00:01:33.330
With this app, you can create ads,

37
00:01:33.330 --> 00:01:35.460
stickers, banners, posters,

38
00:01:35.460 --> 00:01:38.700
and other visuals to help
you sell your product.

39
00:01:38.700 --> 00:01:40.920
This app speeds up the creative process

40
00:01:40.920 --> 00:01:42.630
so you can create custom assets

41
00:01:42.630 --> 00:01:45.540
for every segment of your audience.

42
00:01:45.540 --> 00:01:46.650
The third app we'll build

43
00:01:46.650 --> 00:01:49.710
is what I like to call
an interactive dashboard.

44
00:01:49.710 --> 00:01:52.650
With this app, you'll be able
to visualize your data fast.

45
00:01:52.650 --> 00:01:54.690
No more static graphs or charts

46
00:01:54.690 --> 00:01:56.430
you have to refresh every day.

47
00:01:56.430 --> 00:01:59.340
This app keeps your data
visualizations fresh

48
00:01:59.340 --> 00:02:02.163
so that anyone can get
answers when they need them.

49
00:02:03.090 --> 00:02:04.530
Feeling excited?

50
00:02:04.530 --> 00:02:06.690
Before we dive in, I want to introduce you

51
00:02:06.690 --> 00:02:10.470
to a new AI tool, Google AI Studio.

52
00:02:10.470 --> 00:02:12.480
At Google, I lead an incredible team

53
00:02:12.480 --> 00:02:15.210
of engineers, designers,
and product managers

54
00:02:15.210 --> 00:02:17.940
who help craft the experience in AI Studio

55
00:02:17.940 --> 00:02:19.980
whenever there's a new AI model

56
00:02:19.980 --> 00:02:23.880
or capability that is released
so that people like you

57
00:02:23.880 --> 00:02:26.280
understand how to make the most of it.

58
00:02:26.280 --> 00:02:29.340
We'll use AI Studio to build our apps.

59
00:02:29.340 --> 00:02:34.170
To access it, go to aistudio.google.com.

60
00:02:34.170 --> 00:02:36.240
Once you get there, you'll notice the page

61
00:02:36.240 --> 00:02:38.250
is a bit different from Gemini,

62
00:02:38.250 --> 00:02:41.850
so let's take a second
to walk through the tool.

63
00:02:41.850 --> 00:02:45.720
AI Studio starts on a home
screen with a few main options.

64
00:02:45.720 --> 00:02:46.800
The first is chat,

65
00:02:46.800 --> 00:02:49.770
where you'll write your
prompts to get an output.

66
00:02:49.770 --> 00:02:50.610
On the right side,

67
00:02:50.610 --> 00:02:53.550
you'll see settings to
modify your outputs.

68
00:02:53.550 --> 00:02:55.590
You can select from all
of the newest models

69
00:02:55.590 --> 00:02:56.970
to complete your task,

70
00:02:56.970 --> 00:02:59.520
add system instructions
that the model processes

71
00:02:59.520 --> 00:03:02.250
before using your prompt
to provide output,

72
00:03:02.250 --> 00:03:04.830
adjust the temperature, and more.

73
00:03:04.830 --> 00:03:06.300
Next, we have build,

74
00:03:06.300 --> 00:03:09.690
which is where we'll spend
our time in this course.

75
00:03:09.690 --> 00:03:12.150
When you select the build
function to create an app,

76
00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:14.490
you'll see a text box at the top.

77
00:03:14.490 --> 00:03:18.030
This is where I'll prompt
Gemini models to vibe code.

78
00:03:18.030 --> 00:03:20.160
It works just like the other AI tools,

79
00:03:20.160 --> 00:03:23.640
but this time we'll direct
it to build the three apps.

80
00:03:23.640 --> 00:03:26.490
To vibe code your own app,
you can either write a prompt

81
00:03:26.490 --> 00:03:29.010
or use one of the samples below.

82
00:03:29.010 --> 00:03:33.270
As we build each app, pay close
attention to a few things.

83
00:03:33.270 --> 00:03:35.700
Notice the natural flow of conversation

84
00:03:35.700 --> 00:03:38.100
between you and AI Studio.

85
00:03:38.100 --> 00:03:39.960
You'll iterate by using plain language

86
00:03:39.960 --> 00:03:43.020
to describe what you need
to refine requirements,

87
00:03:43.020 --> 00:03:46.830
to test the output, and
to improve the result.

88
00:03:46.830 --> 00:03:48.787
Next, pay attention to how specific

89
00:03:48.787 --> 00:03:51.210
you'll need to get with your feedback.

90
00:03:51.210 --> 00:03:54.900
That's because vague descriptions
yield generic results.

91
00:03:54.900 --> 00:03:57.720
The more precise you are when
describing what you need,

92
00:03:57.720 --> 00:04:01.020
the more likely the app will
match what you're looking for.

93
00:04:01.020 --> 00:04:04.890
You are the director, user,
and tester of your app,

94
00:04:04.890 --> 00:04:07.503
and now you can use AI
as your developer tool.

95
00:04:08.370 --> 00:04:10.260
Finally, the coolest part.

96
00:04:10.260 --> 00:04:11.580
See how fast you'll move

97
00:04:11.580 --> 00:04:14.250
from an idea to a working prototype.

98
00:04:14.250 --> 00:04:16.440
In the time it takes to
have a chat over coffee,

99
00:04:16.440 --> 00:04:18.990
you can go from, "I wish
there was a tool for this,"

100
00:04:18.990 --> 00:04:21.240
to, "Here's my custom solution."

101
00:04:21.240 --> 00:04:22.773
So let me show you how.